    "about":  "Strong leadership today requires more than technical competence. It requires reflective judgement, psychological awareness, ethical decision-making, and the ability to lead people through complexity with confidence and integrity.\nI work with organisations and leaders to develop inclusive, human-centred leadership cultures that strengthen people, practice, and organisational effectiveness.\nI bring together deep academic expertise and practical leadership experience, holding a Doctorate in Education, a Master’s in Educational Leadership, CIPD certification, and a Postgraduate Diploma in Coaching. My professional background includes curriculum and qualification design, organisational change, executive and leadership coaching, and talent development. A published researcher and writer, I embed inclusive  practices and principles into everything I do and I am known for my engaging, thoughtful, and impactful delivery.  I am a trusted trainer, facilitator, and advisor who equips organisations to lead inclusively, develop people effectively, and achieve lasting, values-driven change.",
